Ulf,

A burner-stabilized flame is not adiabatic, due to heat loss by  
conduction to the burner surface. As the flow rate increases, this  
conduction loss becomes less significant and the final temperature  
increases. As the mass flow rate approaches the limiting value at which  
the flame detaches from the burner, the flame approaches adiabatic.

Dave

